  <section id="home" class="hero">
    <h2>The Ultimate Poker Twist</h2>
    <p>A new strategic poker variant where your hidden Lock Card can change everything.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="how">
    <h2>How to Play</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Each player is dealt 3 cards.</li>
      <li>Choose 1 to be your hidden Lock Card (must be used).</li>
      <li>You may swap 1 Flexi Card (once total).</li>
      <li>Three community cards are revealed (Flop).</li>
      <li>Optional Flexi Card swap again (if not done already).</li>
      <li>Final 2 community cards revealed (Turn & River).</li>
      <li>Betting happens throughout, like Texas Hold’em.</li>
      <li>Pay to reveal someone’s Lock Card if desired.</li>
      <li>Best hand using Lock + 1 Flexi + 3 community wins!</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section id="strategy">
    <h2>Strategy Tips</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Use the Lock Card wisely — it locks your potential.</li>
      <li>Swapping can save you, but don’t waste it early.</li>
      <li>Paying to reveal a Lock Card is powerful late-game.</li>
      <li>Bluffing with a bad-looking Flexi hand can work!</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <h4>Do I have to use my Lock Card?</h4>
    <p>Yes. Your Lock Card must be part of your final 5-card hand.</p>

    <h4>Can I swap more than one Flexi card?</h4>
    <p>No. You may only swap **one** Flexi card during the whole hand (before or after the flop).</p>

    <h4>How much does it cost to reveal a Lock Card?</h4>
    <p>House rules apply, but we suggest 2x the Big Blind into the pot.</p>
  </section>

